was created by another processor.

The procedure @code{wrong-processor-c-return-exception?} returns @code{#t}
when @var{obj} is a wrong-processor-c-return-exception object and @code{#f}
otherwise.

@end deffn

@node Exception objects related to the reader, Exception objects related to evaluation and compilation, Exception objects related to C-interface, Exceptions
